<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="69" type="collection and habitat data">
<paragraph pageId="2" pageNumber="69">Collection and habitat data.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="2" pageNumber="69">
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Psephenidae" genus="Ectopria" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Ectopria nervosa" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="69" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nervosa">Ectopria nervosa</taxonomicName>
was collected at an ultraviolet light and in an ultraviolet light trap deployed in a mature hardwood forest and a mixed forest. Small spring-fed brooks were in the vicinity of the sites where the lights were used. Two individuals were swept from foliage along a river margin (clear, fast-flowing, rocky river). Adults were captured during June and July in New Brunswick.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
